Web applications are everywhere. Every service you use — banking, shopping, government portals, social media — runs as a web application. They are also where the majority of real-world breaches happen.

This chapter covers the most common and impactful web vulnerabilities, how they work, and how to find them using Burp Suite and free practice labs. Everything here builds on the tools introduced in Chapter 04. If you have not yet set up Burp Suite, go back and do that first.

The best free resource for everything in this chapter is the **PortSwigger Web Security Academy** at https://portswigger.net/web-security. It was built by the same people who made Burp Suite, it is completely free, and every topic comes with a hands-on lab using a real vulnerable application. This chapter will direct you to specific labs throughout.

