## Command Injection

Command injection occurs when an application passes user-supplied input to a system shell command without sanitisation. If the application runs `ping INPUT` and you enter `8.8.8.8; whoami`, both commands may execute — and you will see the output of `whoami` in the response.

Command injection is one of the most critical vulnerabilities. Successful exploitation typically gives direct access to the underlying server.

**How to find it:** Look for features that interact with the operating system — IP lookup tools, domain queries, file conversion utilities, image processing features. Test with payloads like `; ls`, `| whoami`, or `&& id` appended to expected input.

**Practice:** https://portswigger.net/web-security/os-command-injection

