## DVWA — Damn Vulnerable Web Application

For local practice without internet, **DVWA** (Damn Vulnerable Web Application) is a PHP application deliberately built with every common vulnerability. It has difficulty settings — low, medium, and high — that adjust how obvious the vulnerabilities are.

Install it on Kali using `sudo apt install dvwa` or download from https://github.com/digininja/DVWA.

DVWA lets you practice SQL injection, XSS, command injection, file upload, CSRF, and more in a completely safe offline environment. After exploiting each vulnerability at low difficulty, switch to medium and try again — it forces you to bypass basic defences and builds a much deeper understanding.

