## A Practical Learning Path for This Chapter

Do not try to learn all of these vulnerability types at once. Go deep on one at a time.

**Week 1 — SQL Injection:** Complete every apprentice-level SQL injection lab on the Web Security Academy. Practice using Burp Repeater to test manually before using SQLmap.

**Week 2 — XSS:** Complete the reflected and stored XSS apprentice labs. Understand the difference between all three types. Practice in DVWA at low difficulty, then medium.

**Week 3 — Access Control:** Complete the IDOR and access control labs. This is the most impactful category for bug bounty work — build strong intuition for it.

**Week 4 — Authentication:** Complete the authentication labs. Set up a local login form and practice Hydra against it to understand what brute-force protection actually prevents.

One hour a day, every day, for a month. By the end of it, you will have a level of practical web security understanding that most people who have only read about this topic will not have.

